post_text:
Voting for Team Up 4 Community’s Spring Challenge begins tomorrow, 5/1 at 9 a.m. and ends at 8 p.m. on 5/8. Summit Lane has their submission from their Hoops for Heart Fundraiser and MacArthur High School has their submission from Autism Awareness Month included in this challenge.

Please spread the word on voting for a chance to win money for the schools! You can vote for as many entries as you choose, but only one vote can be cast per entry per day per valid email address: https://www.teamup4community.org/l-i-spring-sports-heroes-video-challenge-2018

Just as a reminder, $5,000 in Scholarships & Grants will be awarded!
-First Place Winner receives a $3,000 scholarship or grant.

-Second Place Winner receives a $1,500 scholarship or grant.

-Third Place Winner receives a $500 scholarship or grant.

Winners will be announced on or about May 10, 2018.

post_text:
You're Invited to District Instrumental Music Night

Music is everywhere! We hear it at home, in the car, at the mall, on television, in concert halls, and even at sporting events. It is one of the most pervasive experiences in today's world. Students will soon be registering for instrumental music for the 2018-2019 school year. To help children select an appropriate instrument and to provide parents with details about our program, we would like to invite you and your child to attend our annual District Instrumental Music Night on Monday April 30th, 2018 at 7:00 PM.

http://www.levittownschools.com/news/2017-2018/story.asp?xml=2018-03-15_youre_invited_to_district_instrumental_music_night.xml

post_text:
GC Tech's Annual Competition!

GC Tech's Annual Competition will be held in the gym of Levittown Memorial Education Center today, Thursday, February 8th at 6 PM. The entire Levittown community and our extended GC Tech families from across the Long Island region are all welcome to attend this magnificent event that showcases the talents of our amazing students. The competition takes place from 6-8pm with an award ceremony immediately following in our Auditorium. Feel free to arrive at any time and see our students in action demonstrating skills in areas such as Cosmetology, Electrical Technology, Police Science, Culinary Arts and more! Thank you and hope to see you there. Be sure to check our website for updates.

http://www.levittownschools.com

post_text: A Free Youth Heart Screening (ECG and Echocardiogram) for young people ages 12-24 will take place at the LMEC Gym on Abbey Lane on Saturday, Oct. 25 from 9 a.m. - 3 p.m. Testing takes about 35 minutes. There should be no physical exertion for one hour prior to the screening. Questionnaire should be filled out prior to appointment; parent signature required for under 18. Walk-ins accompanied by a parent will be accepted. For more information please visit our website at www.levittownschools.com

post_text:
On Friday, November 8, we will be conducting our state required emergency sheltering and early dismissal drill.

Students will be assembled in the designated sheltering areas in their building and will then be dismissed approximately ten minutes earlier.

Students in the GCTech program will be dismissed thirty minutes earlier.

Transportation will be adjusted for all students who are eligible for bus services.
